00:19:03.700 --> 00:19:05.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And so that
you are what you have--

00:19:05.620 --> 00:19:06.828 align:middle line:90%
big, conspicuous consumption.

00:19:06.828 --> 00:19:09.380 align:middle line:84%
If you've got a big
house, a big car,

00:19:09.380 --> 00:19:12.060 align:middle line:84%
you've got kids in
private schools,

00:19:12.060 --> 00:19:13.150 align:middle line:90%
then you're sophisticated.

00:19:13.150 --> 00:19:13.950 align:middle line:90%
You're an elite.

00:19:13.950 --> 00:19:15.200 align:middle line:90%
You're of value.

00:19:15.200 --> 00:19:17.390 align:middle line:84%
And he said that this
is all being supported

00:19:17.390 --> 00:19:20.750 align:middle line:84%
by a philosophy of
post-modernism, which destroys

00:19:20.750 --> 00:19:22.910 align:middle line:84%
any kind of
epistemological system

00:19:22.910 --> 00:19:25.910 align:middle line:84%
pursuant to which you can
find out what the truth is.

00:19:25.910 --> 00:19:28.220 align:middle line:84%
This has all been
fostered and promoted

00:19:28.220 --> 00:19:29.744 align:middle line:90%
by the national security state.

00:19:29.744 --> 00:19:31.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, let's get to
that now and look at some

00:19:31.910 --> 00:19:34.460 align:middle line:84%
overlays directly how
it's being reflected.

00:19:34.460 --> 00:19:36.740 align:middle line:84%
But first, a philosophical
talk about this.

00:19:36.740 --> 00:19:37.610 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah.

00:19:37.610 --> 00:19:39.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We have become--

00:19:39.170 --> 00:19:43.340 align:middle line:84%
the public at large, I
think, people in general,

00:19:43.340 --> 00:19:45.190 align:middle line:90%
tend to have been easily led.

00:19:45.190 --> 00:19:46.940 align:middle line:84%
I think from the
beginning of our history,

00:19:46.940 --> 00:19:50.000 align:middle line:84%
people tend to be
somewhat easily led

00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:53.780 align:middle line:84%
because there's a certain
trusting aspect of humanity

00:19:53.780 --> 00:19:56.720 align:middle line:84%
in anything that resembles
authority, which has really

00:19:56.720 --> 00:20:00.440 align:middle line:84%
negated any ability to
have nuanced thinking.

00:20:00.440 --> 00:20:05.210 align:middle line:84%
And this, to me, I'm seeing
more and more really important--

00:20:05.210 --> 00:20:07.250 align:middle line:84%
the fact that
people are complex,

00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:10.280 align:middle line:84%
that agendas are complex,
human beings are complex.

00:20:10.280 --> 00:20:16.340 align:middle line:84%
You can have someone who
has maybe in the public view

00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:19.970 align:middle line:84%
done something that
is not good, right?

00:20:19.970 --> 00:20:22.247 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, we
already know historically

00:20:22.247 --> 00:20:24.080 align:middle line:84%
some things that they
have done or that they

00:20:24.080 --> 00:20:26.750 align:middle line:84%
have worked on behalf of
that are quite beneficial

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:28.010 align:middle line:90%
to humankind.

00:20:28.010 --> 00:20:29.720 align:middle line:84%
Yet the headline's
going to grab what's

00:20:29.720 --> 00:20:33.080 align:middle line:84%
been done that's not good
in the eyes of the public,

00:20:33.080 --> 00:20:37.480 align:middle line:84%
and we no longer are capable of
seeing the rest of the story.

00:20:37.480 --> 00:20:39.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm just using that as a
very simplistic example,

00:20:39.770 --> 00:20:41.900 align:middle line:84%
but it's happening
across the board.

00:20:41.900 --> 00:20:47.230 align:middle line:84%
We can't think in nuanced
ways as a culture anymore.

00:20:47.230 --> 00:20:50.440 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: This is
a problem because--

00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:51.350 align:middle line:90%
Rudolf Steiner--

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:52.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, big fan.

00:20:52.840 --> 00:20:58.300 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: --said that if you
allow the state government

00:20:58.300 --> 00:21:01.480 align:middle line:84%
to run the schools,
they will not

00:21:01.480 --> 00:21:04.570 align:middle line:84%
train the students
to think critically,

00:21:04.570 --> 00:21:08.260 align:middle line:84%
because they do not want
the government criticized.

00:21:08.260 --> 00:21:10.540 align:middle line:90%
And that's what's happened.

00:21:10.540 --> 00:21:13.030 align:middle line:84%
Since the end of World
War II and the rise

00:21:13.030 --> 00:21:15.880 align:middle line:84%
of this national
security state, that you

00:21:15.880 --> 00:21:18.190 align:middle line:84%
have to stand up at the
beginning of the class

00:21:18.190 --> 00:21:20.560 align:middle line:84%
and pledge allegiance
to the flag.

00:21:20.560 --> 00:21:22.220 align:middle line:84%
They used to have
prayers in schools

00:21:22.220 --> 00:21:25.540 align:middle line:84%
so that they were promoting
Christianity over all the rest

00:21:25.540 --> 00:21:27.110 align:middle line:90%
of the different religions.

00:21:27.110 --> 00:21:30.790 align:middle line:84%
So Christianity and nationalism
became kind of melded together

00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:34.570 align:middle line:84%
as a patriotic thing
to be Christian here

00:21:34.570 --> 00:21:35.740 align:middle line:90%
in the United States.

00:21:35.740 --> 00:21:37.840 align:middle line:84%
And if you ask any
questions about it

00:21:37.840 --> 00:21:41.026 align:middle line:84%
or challenge it in any
way, you're unpatriotic.

00:21:41.026 --> 00:21:44.290 align:middle line:84%
And so that we began to
generate is a state-run system

00:21:44.290 --> 00:21:48.520 align:middle line:84%
of schools that didn't
really question the authority

00:21:48.520 --> 00:21:50.875 align:middle line:84%
and didn't think
in a nuanced way.

00:21:50.875 --> 00:21:52.750 align:middle line:84%
And they were really,
again, basically trying

00:21:52.750 --> 00:21:55.840 align:middle line:84%
to train the people
to be part of the cogs

00:21:55.840 --> 00:21:58.180 align:middle line:84%
in this corporate machine
so they could get a better

00:21:58.180 --> 00:21:59.545 align:middle line:90%
job working for corporations.

00:21:59.545 --> 00:22:01.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the
question is now,

00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:05.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, other than the obvious,
educate your children privately

00:22:05.260 --> 00:22:06.219 align:middle line:90%
or however you see fit.

00:22:06.219 --> 00:22:07.343 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Homeschool them.

00:22:07.343 --> 00:22:08.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Homeschool
them, exactly.

00:22:08.920 --> 00:22:14.560 align:middle line:84%
Now we have, en masse, a
real problem of very simple

00:22:14.560 --> 00:22:15.894 align:middle line:90%
thinkers, in general.

00:22:15.894 --> 00:22:16.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Simplistic.

00:22:16.810 --> 00:22:17.685 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Simplistic.

00:22:17.685 --> 00:22:18.940 align:middle line:90%
Not to say simple-minded.

00:22:18.940 --> 00:22:19.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Not
simple-minded, simplistic.

00:22:19.800 --> 00:22:21.550 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Right,
simplistic thinking.

00:22:21.550 --> 00:22:23.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and what they
will embrace as a viewpoint.

00:22:23.940 --> 00:22:24.940 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:22:24.940 --> 00:22:27.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We need to look
at, for a moment here,

00:22:27.040 --> 00:22:28.540 align:middle line:84%
at the way out of
that before we go

00:22:28.540 --> 00:22:31.774 align:middle line:84%
into this overlay of deception
in our current situation.

00:22:31.774 --> 00:22:33.190 align:middle line:84%
How do we find our
way out of that

00:22:33.190 --> 00:22:35.890 align:middle line:84%
and develop discernment
and nuanced thinking again?

00:22:35.890 --> 00:22:39.880 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: I think that one of
the best opportunities that we

00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:43.840 align:middle line:84%
have now is a number of the
major private universities

00:22:43.840 --> 00:22:48.610 align:middle line:84%
in the country are starting
to put their courses online,

00:22:48.610 --> 00:22:51.490 align:middle line:84%
and that people can
actually go online,

00:22:51.490 --> 00:22:54.040 align:middle line:84%
if they will take
the time to do it,

00:22:54.040 --> 00:22:57.880 align:middle line:84%
and they can actually sit
and participate in the class.

00:22:57.880 --> 00:23:00.974 align:middle line:84%
They can watch the class, the
lecture, being broadcast live.

00:23:00.974 --> 00:23:02.515 align:middle line:84%
They can listen to
the questions that

00:23:02.515 --> 00:23:04.570 align:middle line:84%
are being asked by the
students, et cetera.

00:23:04.570 --> 00:23:09.430 align:middle line:84%
People have access now to an
independent private education

00:23:09.430 --> 00:23:11.404 align:middle line:84%
if they will take
the time to do this.

00:23:11.404 --> 00:23:12.820 align:middle line:84%
But the problem
is is that they're

00:23:12.820 --> 00:23:17.470 align:middle line:84%
being bombarded on television
with sports and soap

00:23:17.470 --> 00:23:22.030 align:middle line:84%
operas and game shows and
all these distracting kind

00:23:22.030 --> 00:23:25.700 align:middle line:84%
of shiny things to
attract their attention.

00:23:25.700 --> 00:23:29.740 align:middle line:84%
And I think that, for
example, the courses--

00:23:29.740 --> 00:23:31.900 align:middle line:84%
I teach a course
every single spring

00:23:31.900 --> 00:23:36.060 align:middle line:84%
at the University of California
in Santa Cruz, California.

00:23:36.060 --> 00:23:40.330 align:middle line:84%
And that people can go on our
website, the Romero Institute,

00:23:40.330 --> 00:23:44.370 align:middle line:84%
romeroinstitute.org, and they
can just click on Classes.

00:23:44.370 --> 00:23:50.140 align:middle line:84%
And for example, I deliver
20 90-minute lectures

00:23:50.140 --> 00:23:52.720 align:middle line:84%
on the assassination
of President Kennedy,

00:23:52.720 --> 00:23:55.300 align:middle line:84%
reviewing all of the
alternative theories,

00:23:55.300 --> 00:23:57.500 align:middle line:84%
laying out all of the
positive and negative aspects

00:23:57.500 --> 00:23:58.120 align:middle line:90%
to each of the theories.

00:23:58.120 --> 00:23:59.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To lead people to
come to their conclusion.

00:23:59.140 --> 00:24:00.370 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: So people
can look at this

00:24:00.370 --> 00:24:02.630 align:middle line:84%
and decide what it is they
think happened here, OK?

00:24:02.630 --> 00:24:03.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:03.430 --> 00:24:04.888 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: I've
done the same thing

00:24:04.888 --> 00:24:06.920 align:middle line:84%
with a number of other
different issues.

00:24:06.920 --> 00:24:09.610 align:middle line:84%
And so that's just one kind
of course that's available.

00:24:09.610 --> 00:24:10.945 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I've heard
that some universities--

00:24:10.945 --> 00:24:13.660 align:middle line:84%
I've read that some universities
are actually now starting

00:24:13.660 --> 00:24:16.210 align:middle line:84%
to put classes that
are essentially

00:24:16.210 --> 00:24:18.557 align:middle line:84%
the philosophy of truth
back on the menu--

00:24:18.557 --> 00:24:19.390 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: They are.

00:24:19.390 --> 00:24:20.080 align:middle line:90%
They are.

00:24:20.080 --> 00:24:21.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --because
it's been so distorted.

00:24:21.620 --> 00:24:23.786 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, we're
working out at the University

00:24:23.786 --> 00:24:25.864 align:middle line:84%
of California to try to
get critical thinking--

00:24:25.864 --> 00:24:27.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Critical thinking.

00:24:27.030 --> 00:24:28.030 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: --entire courses on--

00:24:28.030 --> 00:24:28.905 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:24:28.905 --> 00:24:30.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: --critical thinking.

00:24:30.850 --> 00:24:33.850 align:middle line:90%
So I think there's hope here.

00:24:33.850 --> 00:24:35.710 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to overstate
the problem here.

00:24:35.710 --> 00:24:37.720 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that
the national security

00:24:37.720 --> 00:24:41.050 align:middle line:84%
state here in the United
States has gotten itself firmly

00:24:41.050 --> 00:24:42.550 align:middle line:90%
in control.

00:24:42.550 --> 00:24:46.510 align:middle line:84%
You saw us rise up against it
with the Pentagon Papers case.

00:24:46.510 --> 00:24:50.690 align:middle line:84%
You saw us rise up against
it with the Iran-Contra case.

00:24:50.690 --> 00:24:54.320 align:middle line:84%
We generated-- the churches and
synagogues around the country

00:24:54.320 --> 00:24:57.410 align:middle line:84%
generated the American sanctuary
movement to bring people in

00:24:57.410 --> 00:25:00.400 align:middle line:84%
out of South America that were
being targeted by these regimes

00:25:00.400 --> 00:25:02.770 align:middle line:84%
that the CIA create
down there, and they

00:25:02.770 --> 00:25:05.515 align:middle line:90%
were sharing the information.

00:25:05.515 --> 00:25:07.660 align:middle line:84%
We're within striking
distance of being

00:25:07.660 --> 00:25:09.496 align:middle line:90%
able to pull out of this thing.

00:25:09.496 --> 00:25:10.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I think so.

00:25:10.370 --> 00:25:12.280 align:middle line:84%
Also, you have a couple
of young sons, or--

00:25:12.280 --> 00:25:13.080 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yes.

00:25:13.080 --> 00:25:15.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --youngish,
younger than you, right?

00:25:15.420 --> 00:25:19.000 align:middle line:84%
And in any event, I
see a great amount

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:21.880 align:middle line:84%
of hope just in that
generation alone, because, A,

00:25:21.880 --> 00:25:24.120 align:middle line:90%
they're turning off media.

00:25:24.120 --> 00:25:25.870 align:middle line:84%
But they're going
to their own sources

00:25:25.870 --> 00:25:28.910 align:middle line:84%
that they resonate with so that
they're still in that matrix,

00:25:28.910 --> 00:25:36.460 align:middle line:84%
but they tend to not buy
into the larger public story.

00:25:36.460 --> 00:25:39.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, there's two
generations of our children.

00:25:39.890 --> 00:25:41.980 align:middle line:84%
The children that
were born earlier

00:25:41.980 --> 00:25:44.600 align:middle line:84%
are in the X
Generation, and the ones

00:25:44.600 --> 00:25:46.060 align:middle line:84%
that have been
born more recently

00:25:46.060 --> 00:25:47.590 align:middle line:84%
are in the Millennial
Generation.

00:25:47.590 --> 00:25:49.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, my son's right
on the edge of the Millennials.

00:25:49.360 --> 00:25:50.360 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:25:50.360 --> 00:25:54.760 align:middle line:84%
And the Millennials are quite
progressive and quite creative.

00:25:54.760 --> 00:25:55.570 align:middle line:90%
In fact, 83%--

00:25:55.570 --> 00:25:56.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they're
not buying the stories.

00:25:56.820 --> 00:25:57.736 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: No, no, no.

00:25:57.736 --> 00:26:01.910 align:middle line:84%
83% of them voted for Bernie
Sanders in the primaries.

00:26:01.910 --> 00:26:02.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:26:02.710 --> 00:26:03.350 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And they're
saying, look it,

00:26:03.350 --> 00:26:05.170 align:middle line:90%
they want progressive solutions.

00:26:05.170 --> 00:26:08.464 align:middle line:84%
They can see through a
lot of this propaganda.

00:26:08.464 --> 00:26:10.630 align:middle line:84%
They know that we need to
have a single-payer health

00:26:10.630 --> 00:26:14.050 align:middle line:84%
system, like most of the other
civilized major industrial

00:26:14.050 --> 00:26:16.045 align:middle line:90%
countries have.

00:26:16.045 --> 00:26:17.200 align:middle line:90%
They're quite progressive.

00:26:17.200 --> 00:26:20.200 align:middle line:84%
The X Generation,
however, has been caught

00:26:20.200 --> 00:26:21.630 align:middle line:90%
right in this kind of cynicism.

00:26:21.630 --> 00:26:22.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:22.430 --> 00:26:24.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That they
don't believe people.

00:26:24.040 --> 00:26:25.300 align:middle line:90%
They don't believe anybody.

00:26:25.300 --> 00:26:28.390 align:middle line:84%
And so that they think that
getting ahead financially

00:26:28.390 --> 00:26:30.970 align:middle line:90%
is the only solid plan for them.

00:26:30.970 --> 00:26:32.140 align:middle line:90%
And so that they're looking.

00:26:32.140 --> 00:26:33.170 align:middle line:90%
They go to Wall Street.

00:26:33.170 --> 00:26:35.170 align:middle line:90%
They become bond salesmen.

00:26:35.170 --> 00:26:36.550 align:middle line:90%
They do these things.

00:26:36.550 --> 00:26:38.570 align:middle line:90%
And we're engaged in a process.

00:26:38.570 --> 00:26:41.710 align:middle line:84%
The Baby Boom Generation and
the Millennial Generation,

00:26:41.710 --> 00:26:43.780 align:middle line:84%
are basically
involved in a project

00:26:43.780 --> 00:26:46.360 align:middle line:84%
of trying to help
the X Generation get

00:26:46.360 --> 00:26:47.705 align:middle line:90%
past this kind of cynical--

00:26:47.705 --> 00:26:48.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:26:48.580 --> 00:26:49.900 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: --lack
of belief in things.

00:26:49.900 --> 00:26:51.941 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, an
interesting thing, too, again,

00:26:51.941 --> 00:26:54.670 align:middle line:84%
this lack of nuanced
thinking, a headline

00:26:54.670 --> 00:26:56.380 align:middle line:84%
that came up
recently as a result

00:26:56.380 --> 00:26:59.380 align:middle line:84%
of the shooting at the
congressional baseball game,

00:26:59.380 --> 00:27:04.150 align:middle line:90%
right, of a Republican.

00:27:04.150 --> 00:27:06.580 align:middle line:84%
Bernie Sanders is
now coming under fire

00:27:06.580 --> 00:27:09.550 align:middle line:84%
because this man was
a volunteer for him.

00:27:09.550 --> 00:27:10.960 align:middle line:90%
So what's the press do?

00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:13.420 align:middle line:84%
They take off and riff
on the fact this guy

00:27:13.420 --> 00:27:14.870 align:middle line:90%
volunteered for Bernie Sanders.

00:27:14.870 --> 00:27:16.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, Newt
Gingrich came out with it.

00:27:16.510 --> 00:27:17.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:27:17.310 --> 00:27:20.260 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: So what you
have is that there's

00:27:20.260 --> 00:27:24.160 align:middle line:84%
a kind of choreography
of this kind of coloring

00:27:24.160 --> 00:27:26.050 align:middle line:84%
of every story that
comes out to have

00:27:26.050 --> 00:27:30.460 align:middle line:84%
to put it into this dialectical,
confrontational mode.

00:27:30.460 --> 00:27:33.010 align:middle line:84%
And Newt Gingrich came
straight out immediately,

00:27:33.010 --> 00:27:35.170 align:middle line:84%
started saying, look it,
you remember this guy

00:27:35.170 --> 00:27:36.620 align:middle line:90%
volunteered for Bernie Sanders.

00:27:36.620 --> 00:27:36.930 align:middle line:90%
See what they're--

00:27:36.930 --> 00:27:38.300 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like this
was Bernie's fault now.

00:27:38.300 --> 00:27:38.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: --yeah, then
you see what they're like.

00:27:38.970 --> 00:27:41.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the
programming is just--

00:27:41.010 --> 00:27:42.320 align:middle line:90%
it's almost laughable.

00:27:42.320 --> 00:27:44.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well,
because that one

00:27:44.770 --> 00:27:52.150 align:middle line:84%
