00:37:01.354 --> 00:37:02.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Can it be revived?

00:37:02.520 --> 00:37:03.540 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: It can.

00:37:03.540 --> 00:37:05.510 align:middle line:84%
And so that if in
fact the president

00:37:05.510 --> 00:37:07.280 align:middle line:84%
tried to fire
Mueller now, which he

00:37:07.280 --> 00:37:08.600 align:middle line:84%
has the constitutional
authority to do--

00:37:08.600 --> 00:37:09.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He's threatened to.

00:37:09.440 --> 00:37:10.240 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:13.040 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, it's not clear.

00:37:13.040 --> 00:37:17.670 align:middle line:84%
Newt Gingrich has said, that
the president is discussing this

00:37:17.670 --> 00:37:19.294 align:middle line:90%
and his authority to do this.

00:37:19.294 --> 00:37:20.835 align:middle line:84%
And that set up this
kind of wildfire

00:37:20.835 --> 00:37:23.450 align:middle line:84%
by other people being
worried he might do it.

00:37:23.450 --> 00:37:26.870 align:middle line:84%
If he were to do that, then
Congress could then simply

00:37:26.870 --> 00:37:31.240 align:middle line:84%
convene and reenact the
special prosecutor statute,

00:37:31.240 --> 00:37:35.600 align:middle line:84%
re-establish a special
select group of the judges

00:37:35.600 --> 00:37:38.510 align:middle line:84%
on the Court of Appeals for
the District of Columbia,

00:37:38.510 --> 00:37:41.030 align:middle line:84%
and have them appoint an
independent prosecutor.

00:37:41.030 --> 00:37:43.519 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But wouldn't that
require bipartisanship?

00:37:43.519 --> 00:37:44.560 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yes, it would.

00:37:44.560 --> 00:37:46.940 align:middle line:84%
And so the question is
really is whether enough

00:37:46.940 --> 00:37:50.180 align:middle line:84%
of the Republican
members of Congress

00:37:50.180 --> 00:37:54.570 align:middle line:84%
would be so offended by the
president firing Mueller

00:37:54.570 --> 00:37:56.490 align:middle line:84%
that they would
agree to do this.

00:37:56.490 --> 00:37:59.660 align:middle line:84%
And that's the operational
question that's on the floor

00:37:59.660 --> 00:38:00.470 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:38:00.470 --> 00:38:03.010 align:middle line:84%
Is if, in fact, the
president were to do that,

00:38:03.010 --> 00:38:05.300 align:middle line:84%
would there be enough
support from the Republicans

00:38:05.300 --> 00:38:08.630 align:middle line:84%
in Congress to enact a new
special prosecutor act?

00:38:08.630 --> 00:38:11.030 align:middle line:84%
And if they did,
it's almost certain

00:38:11.030 --> 00:38:12.770 align:middle line:84%
that the person who
would be appointed

00:38:12.770 --> 00:38:14.990 align:middle line:90%
would be Robert Mueller again.

00:38:14.990 --> 00:38:16.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There you go.

00:38:16.020 --> 00:38:17.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And so that what
they would be doing is saying,

00:38:17.620 --> 00:38:19.700 align:middle line:84%
see you can't get
away with doing that,

00:38:19.700 --> 00:38:21.710 align:middle line:84%
even though you can get
away with doing that.

00:38:21.710 --> 00:38:23.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Kind of like
the travel ban thing.

00:38:23.120 --> 00:38:23.570 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:38:23.570 --> 00:38:25.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You can do it,
but it's not going to hold.

00:38:25.490 --> 00:38:26.865 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: The
judicial branch is

00:38:26.865 --> 00:38:29.360 align:middle line:90%
going to rise up and check you.

00:38:29.360 --> 00:38:31.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's what would
happen I think here,

00:38:31.400 --> 00:38:32.584 align:middle line:90%
if he were to do that.

00:38:32.584 --> 00:38:34.250 align:middle line:84%
Now what we hear the
latest thing for us

00:38:34.250 --> 00:38:37.580 align:middle line:84%
that we hear is not only
that Robert Mueller is

00:38:37.580 --> 00:38:40.070 align:middle line:84%
now for the first
time investigating

00:38:40.070 --> 00:38:43.910 align:middle line:84%
the president himself for
potentially being involved

00:38:43.910 --> 00:38:47.990 align:middle line:84%
in colluding with the
Russians, but specifically

00:38:47.990 --> 00:38:51.740 align:middle line:84%
for obstructing the
investigation by firing

00:38:51.740 --> 00:38:52.700 align:middle line:90%
the Head of the FBI--

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:58.190 align:middle line:84%
Comey-- and going to
the Director of National

00:38:58.190 --> 00:39:00.110 align:middle line:84%
Intelligence and
going to the others

00:39:00.110 --> 00:39:04.970 align:middle line:84%
to try to get them to
pressure the FBI to stop

00:39:04.970 --> 00:39:06.750 align:middle line:90%
the investigation.

00:39:06.750 --> 00:39:12.320 align:middle line:84%
I think that what we can have
is a potential in the 2018

00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:15.770 align:middle line:84%
election and the 2020 election
coming up, to actually

00:39:15.770 --> 00:39:19.460 align:middle line:84%
have a genuinely progressive
alternative that says,

00:39:19.460 --> 00:39:23.520 align:middle line:84%
look everybody agrees that we
want to get past this thing.

00:39:23.520 --> 00:39:26.630 align:middle line:84%
And so that if there is a
genuine independent party--

00:39:26.630 --> 00:39:28.370 align:middle line:84%
not an independent
party that just

00:39:28.370 --> 00:39:30.180 align:middle line:84%
doesn't have any
positions on things

00:39:30.180 --> 00:39:32.300 align:middle line:84%
or just I don't like
either one of them--

00:39:32.300 --> 00:39:34.910 align:middle line:84%
that's not-- I mean, in
a certain sense that's

00:39:34.910 --> 00:39:35.780 align:middle line:90%
independent.

00:39:35.780 --> 00:39:38.510 align:middle line:84%
But what you really have to do
is develop a set of commitments

00:39:38.510 --> 00:39:41.270 align:middle line:84%
to constitutional
principles, a commitment

00:39:41.270 --> 00:39:44.900 align:middle line:84%
to truth and honesty, a
commitment to integrity.

00:39:44.900 --> 00:39:47.990 align:middle line:84%
All the things that
have been pretended

00:39:47.990 --> 00:39:50.550 align:middle line:84%
to be operational in
the United States.

00:39:50.550 --> 00:39:53.180 align:middle line:84%
But what we can do is
we can catch them up

00:39:53.180 --> 00:39:56.130 align:middle line:84%
on this, because they've
always promised that this is

00:39:56.130 --> 00:39:57.680 align:middle line:90%
what the offer is that we have.

00:39:57.680 --> 00:40:00.030 align:middle line:84%
And so if we can just
come forward and say,

00:40:00.030 --> 00:40:03.980 align:middle line:84%
look we're going to have an
independent party that is

00:40:03.980 --> 00:40:07.340 align:middle line:84%
genuinely independent, it is
committed to the bedrock values

00:40:07.340 --> 00:40:10.550 align:middle line:84%
of our American Constitution--
not some reactionary reading

00:40:10.550 --> 00:40:13.700 align:middle line:84%
of the Constitution that took a
photograph of the Constitution

00:40:13.700 --> 00:40:18.830 align:middle line:84%
in 1789, and said, that's an
original interpretation and you

00:40:18.830 --> 00:40:21.540 align:middle line:84%
can't have women's rights,
because they weren't included

00:40:21.540 --> 00:40:23.000 align:middle line:90%
and all of that--

00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:26.510 align:middle line:84%
but a genuinely intentional
and progressive view of this.

00:40:26.510 --> 00:40:28.700 align:middle line:84%
An independent
view that is rooted

00:40:28.700 --> 00:40:30.230 align:middle line:90%
in constitutional scholarship.

00:40:30.230 --> 00:40:34.920 align:middle line:84%
And to begin to elect
a set of legislators

00:40:34.920 --> 00:40:36.750 align:middle line:84%
who are independent
from both sides,

00:40:36.750 --> 00:40:42.120 align:middle line:84%
genuinely, and will hold
control inside the legislatures

00:40:42.120 --> 00:40:45.540 align:middle line:84%
to begin to start to implement
the true vision of the American

00:40:45.540 --> 00:40:47.075 align:middle line:84%
Constitution in
American history.

00:40:47.075 --> 00:40:47.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Hear, hear.

00:40:47.950 --> 00:40:48.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's our chance.

00:40:48.840 --> 00:40:49.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:40:49.440 --> 00:40:50.880 align:middle line:90%
I agree with you wholeheartedly.

00:40:50.880 --> 00:40:54.540 align:middle line:84%
But for now, we have to let
investigations, justice,

00:40:54.540 --> 00:40:55.910 align:middle line:90%
and such play out honestly.

00:40:55.910 --> 00:40:56.910 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:40:56.910 --> 00:40:58.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We haven't
done that in a long time.

00:40:58.110 --> 00:40:58.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: No.

00:40:58.590 --> 00:40:58.680 align:middle line:90%
We have not done that.

00:40:58.680 --> 00:41:00.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It has to
be allowed to proceed.

00:41:00.200 --> 00:41:01.440 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And as
they say, everything

00:41:01.440 --> 00:41:02.774 align:middle line:90%
is politicized in Washington DC.

00:41:02.774 --> 00:41:03.898 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, everything.

00:41:03.898 --> 00:41:05.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And so
that the question

00:41:05.520 --> 00:41:11.510 align:middle line:84%
is whether Mueller is going
to be able to rise above this.

00:41:11.510 --> 00:41:14.670 align:middle line:84%
The reason why both
Republicans, Democrats respect

00:41:14.670 --> 00:41:17.490 align:middle line:84%
him is being said, because
he's genuinely honest,

00:41:17.490 --> 00:41:19.900 align:middle line:90%
generally is a man of integrity.

00:41:19.900 --> 00:41:23.680 align:middle line:84%
So if he lives up
to that billing

00:41:23.680 --> 00:41:27.950 align:middle line:84%
and goes completely through
with this investigation,

00:41:27.950 --> 00:41:32.390 align:middle line:84%
and reveals the
fact that there has

00:41:32.390 --> 00:41:35.560 align:middle line:84%
been this manipulation of the
voting going on for some time,

00:41:35.560 --> 00:41:40.160 align:middle line:84%
and that there needs
to be consequences

00:41:40.160 --> 00:41:42.490 align:middle line:84%
for both the Republican
and Democratic Party.

00:41:42.490 --> 00:41:45.920 align:middle line:84%
That people have to stop
having this blind trust

00:41:45.920 --> 00:41:47.415 align:middle line:90%
in one or the other.

00:41:47.415 --> 00:41:48.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:41:48.290 --> 00:41:51.600 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That they are not
the repositories of truth.

00:41:51.600 --> 00:41:54.250 align:middle line:84%
There needs to be an
independent view of this.

00:41:54.250 --> 00:41:56.270 align:middle line:84%
There needs to be an
independent party.

00:41:56.270 --> 00:41:58.700 align:middle line:84%
There needs to be a party that
takes a complete and close

00:41:58.700 --> 00:42:01.870 align:middle line:84%
honest look at global climate
change, what the evidence is,

00:42:01.870 --> 00:42:04.245 align:middle line:84%
so that you're not trapped in
one extreme view or another

00:42:04.245 --> 00:42:05.045 align:middle line:90%
of this.

00:42:05.045 --> 00:42:06.500 align:middle line:84%
Let's get an honest
view of this.

00:42:06.500 --> 00:42:08.810 align:middle line:84%
To get an honest view
of the issue of how

00:42:08.810 --> 00:42:10.940 align:middle line:84%
we are going to be dealing
with the racial problem

00:42:10.940 --> 00:42:13.010 align:middle line:84%
in our country,
of the racism that

00:42:13.010 --> 00:42:15.977 align:middle line:84%
is a remnant of our
institution of slavery.

00:42:15.977 --> 00:42:18.560 align:middle line:84%
If we're going to have an honest
look at what the consequences

00:42:18.560 --> 00:42:21.940 align:middle line:84%
are of the misogyny
against women

00:42:21.940 --> 00:42:23.900 align:middle line:84%
and have a completely
honest view of what

00:42:23.900 --> 00:42:28.190 align:middle line:84%
this is and the
view of our system.

00:42:28.190 --> 00:42:31.910 align:middle line:84%
We've got to get rid
of the corporations.

00:42:31.910 --> 00:42:35.000 align:middle line:84%
The corporations have only
existed since the Robber Baron

00:42:35.000 --> 00:42:37.370 align:middle line:84%
era, where you have
this thing set up

00:42:37.370 --> 00:42:39.470 align:middle line:84%
where the owners
of the companies

00:42:39.470 --> 00:42:42.830 align:middle line:84%
are completely immunized
against any personal liability,

00:42:42.830 --> 00:42:44.150 align:middle line:90%
because they're stockholders.

00:42:44.150 --> 00:42:46.940 align:middle line:84%
The management is completely
immune from liability.

00:42:46.940 --> 00:42:48.470 align:middle line:84%
The board of directors
is completely

00:42:48.470 --> 00:42:49.690 align:middle line:90%
immune from liability.

00:42:49.690 --> 00:42:52.640 align:middle line:84%
So that only the corporation and
the assets of the corporation

00:42:52.640 --> 00:42:55.190 align:middle line:84%
are all that are potentially
subject to any kind

00:42:55.190 --> 00:42:56.720 align:middle line:90%
of punishment.

00:42:56.720 --> 00:43:00.290 align:middle line:84%
Any sinful structure
like that, just

00:43:00.290 --> 00:43:03.290 align:middle line:84%
as Pope Francis points out
again in his global encyclical

00:43:03.290 --> 00:43:05.120 align:middle line:90%
of June of 2015--

00:43:05.120 --> 00:43:07.700 align:middle line:90%
this is a sinful structure.

00:43:07.700 --> 00:43:09.530 align:middle line:84%
And what it's done
is it's taken control

00:43:09.530 --> 00:43:11.310 align:middle line:90%
of our entire government.

00:43:11.310 --> 00:43:13.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's now set up
a fascist government

00:43:13.760 --> 00:43:17.390 align:middle line:84%
getting our government to be at
the bidding of the corporations

00:43:17.390 --> 00:43:18.920 align:middle line:84%
and the owners of
the corporations.

00:43:18.920 --> 00:43:20.840 align:middle line:84%
We've got to have an
independent party that is

00:43:20.840 --> 00:43:23.210 align:middle line:90%
going to stop the corporations.

00:43:23.210 --> 00:43:25.140 align:middle line:90%
They're created by the state.

00:43:25.140 --> 00:43:26.390 align:middle line:90%
They're a government creation.

00:43:26.390 --> 00:43:29.330 align:middle line:84%
Without a license to
perform like this,

00:43:29.330 --> 00:43:31.410 align:middle line:90%
they're going to be liable.

00:43:31.410 --> 00:43:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And we're not against capitalism
or entrepreneurialism.

00:43:36.740 --> 00:43:38.810 align:middle line:84%
If people want to
have a business,

00:43:38.810 --> 00:43:41.000 align:middle line:84%
and want to make a
reasonable profit,

00:43:41.000 --> 00:43:43.850 align:middle line:84%
and want to be held responsible
for any damages done

00:43:43.850 --> 00:43:47.150 align:middle line:84%
by their business--
fine, let them do that.

00:43:47.150 --> 00:43:49.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the inhumane
practices have to stop,

00:43:49.940 --> 00:43:52.940 align:middle line:84%
because the large
corporations are essentially

00:43:52.940 --> 00:43:54.887 align:middle line:90%
behaving in an inhumane way.

00:43:54.887 --> 00:43:56.470 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: They are
sinful structures.

00:43:56.470 --> 00:43:57.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:43:57.270 --> 00:43:59.810 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And they
need to be taken apart.

00:43:59.810 --> 00:44:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And even the Libertarian Party,
with all of its shortcomings,

00:44:03.440 --> 00:44:07.910 align:middle line:84%
had in its platform
for years that

00:44:07.910 --> 00:44:10.851 align:middle line:84%
the state-sponsored corporations
have to be eliminated.

00:44:10.851 --> 00:44:13.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think most of
the people listening to this

00:44:13.100 --> 00:44:15.190 align:middle line:84%
are on the same page
with you on that one.

00:44:15.190 --> 00:44:15.990 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yes.

00:44:15.990 --> 00:44:17.810 align:middle line:84%
And so what I'm
saying is that there

00:44:17.810 --> 00:44:21.680 align:middle line:84%
are some keys to the
solution to this problem.

00:44:21.680 --> 00:44:24.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think we have to have an
independent party like that.

00:44:24.620 --> 00:44:28.390 align:middle line:84%
I think we need to start
mounting candidates

00:44:28.390 --> 00:44:30.257 align:middle line:84%
and we have to speak
out about this.

00:44:30.257 --> 00:44:32.257 align:middle line:84%
We have to come to grips
with the injustice that

00:44:32.257 --> 00:44:34.771 align:middle line:84%
is being performed to the
Native American people.

00:44:34.771 --> 00:44:37.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're going to get
right on that in just a second.

00:44:37.270 --> 00:44:39.895 align:middle line:84%
But what's beautiful and hopeful
about all this is I'm starting

00:44:39.895 --> 00:44:42.380 align:middle line:84%
to see-- we're all
starting to see--

00:44:42.380 --> 00:44:44.540 align:middle line:84%
incidences around
the country where

00:44:44.540 --> 00:44:47.567 align:middle line:84%
totally unexpected and
unlikely people are popping

00:44:47.567 --> 00:44:48.650 align:middle line:90%
up and running for office.

00:44:48.650 --> 00:44:51.170 align:middle line:84%
And they're just claiming
to be honest citizens that

00:44:51.170 --> 00:44:52.255 align:middle line:90%
are somewhat informed.

00:44:52.255 --> 00:44:52.620 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah.

00:44:52.620 --> 00:44:53.150 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:44:53.150 --> 00:44:54.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And that's beautiful.

00:44:54.050 --> 00:44:55.050 align:middle line:90%
That's how it should be.

00:44:55.050 --> 00:44:56.889 align:middle line:84%
Maybe again then we
can start reflecting

00:44:56.889 --> 00:44:57.930 align:middle line:90%
the wishes of the people.

00:44:57.930 --> 00:44:59.240 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah.

00:44:59.240 --> 00:45:01.790 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that needs to be done

00:45:01.790 --> 00:45:04.670 align:middle line:84%
is to have people
step forward and take

00:45:04.670 --> 00:45:06.690 align:middle line:84%
advantage of the
internet that exists now.

00:45:06.690 --> 00:45:07.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:45:07.490 --> 00:45:08.420 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:45:08.420 --> 00:45:12.500 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: To put these
college courses online

00:45:12.500 --> 00:45:14.475 align:middle line:84%
so that young kids in
their early years--

00:45:14.475 --> 00:45:16.100 align:middle line:84%
in junior high school
and high school--

00:45:16.100 --> 00:45:19.290 align:middle line:84%
can watch these courses,
learn critical thinking.

00:45:19.290 --> 00:45:23.086 align:middle line:84%
Even though their public
schools are run by the state,

00:45:23.086 --> 00:45:24.460 align:middle line:84%
that they can
stand up in class--

00:45:24.460 --> 00:45:25.418 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Self-educate.

00:45:25.418 --> 00:45:27.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: --and say,
look I've seen this thing,

00:45:27.620 --> 00:45:30.016 align:middle line:84%
I don't agree with what
you're saying here.

00:45:30.016 --> 00:45:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And there need to be enough
of them, so they don't say,

00:45:32.370 --> 00:45:34.610 align:middle line:84%
well, you're going to get
expelled, because you're

00:45:34.610 --> 00:45:36.540 align:middle line:84%
disrupting the class,
interfering with what

00:45:36.540 --> 00:45:38.130 align:middle line:90%
we're trying to teach here.

00:45:38.130 --> 00:45:41.240 align:middle line:84%
So I think that the
internet presents

00:45:41.240 --> 00:45:43.400 align:middle line:84%
an extraordinary
opportunity for us

00:45:43.400 --> 00:45:47.280 align:middle line:84%
to establish a genuinely
independent political party

00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:50.210 align:middle line:84%
and to get back to the
bedrock values of the American

00:45:50.210 --> 00:45:53.270 align:middle line:84%
Constitution, and to
share these values

00:45:53.270 --> 00:45:55.610 align:middle line:84%
in an open and honest way
with people around the world.

00:45:55.610 --> 00:45:56.530 align:middle line:90%
Not coerce them.

00:45:56.530 --> 00:45:58.500 align:middle line:90%
Not invade them.

00:45:58.500 --> 00:45:59.870 align:middle line:90%
Not infiltrate them.

00:45:59.870 --> 00:46:02.210 align:middle line:84%
Not set up covert
operations against them.

00:46:02.210 --> 00:46:06.040 align:middle line:84%
You make these options available
for the people of the world

00:46:06.040 --> 00:46:07.790 align:middle line:90%
and see what the people do.

00:46:07.790 --> 00:46:09.245 align:middle line:90%
I think the people will respond.

00:46:09.245 --> 00:46:10.045 align:middle line:90%
I really do.

00:46:10.045 --> 00:46:10.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I do too.

00:46:10.970 --> 00:46:12.350 align:middle line:90%
We're on the same page.

00:46:12.350 --> 00:46:14.120 align:middle line:90%
I see it bright ahead.

00:46:14.120 --> 00:46:16.540 align:middle line:84%
We just have some more muck
to go through looks like.

00:46:16.540 --> 00:46:18.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: We've got a temporary
period of some challenges.

00:46:18.530 --> 00:46:19.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, we do.

00:46:19.340 --> 00:46:20.140 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:46:20.140 --> 00:46:21.440 align:middle line:90%
So let's move on to the Lakota.

00:46:21.440 --> 00:46:23.850 align:middle line:90%
You're their counsel.

00:46:23.850 --> 00:46:27.340 align:middle line:84%
And there was recently
a very hopeful headline

00:46:27.340 --> 00:46:28.862 align:middle line:90%
that came up and--

00:46:28.862 --> 00:46:30.570 align:middle line:84%
we only have a couple
of minutes on that,

00:46:30.570 --> 00:46:32.530 align:middle line:84%
because I want to get
to something really,

00:46:32.530 --> 00:46:33.910 align:middle line:90%
really, really hopeful.

00:46:33.910 --> 00:46:35.150 align:middle line:90%
So tell us what's going on.

00:46:35.150 --> 00:46:38.550 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: On June 14, the
United States District Court

00:46:38.550 --> 00:46:41.050 align:middle line:84%
in Washington DC,
Judge Boasberg,

00:46:41.050 --> 00:46:48.720 align:middle line:84%
entered an opinion stating that
it was unlawful for the US Army

00:46:48.720 --> 00:46:51.900 align:middle line:84%
Corps of Engineers under
the Trump administration

00:46:51.900 --> 00:46:55.170 align:middle line:84%
to have granted a
certificate of easement

00:46:55.170 --> 00:46:57.450 align:middle line:84%
to the Dakota Access
Pipeline to allow them

00:46:57.450 --> 00:47:00.536 align:middle line:84%
to complete construction
and start pumping oil

00:47:00.536 --> 00:47:01.410 align:middle line:90%
through the pipeline.

00:47:01.410 --> 00:47:02.618 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Which they've done.

00:47:02.618 --> 00:47:04.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Which
they've done not

00:47:04.230 --> 00:47:06.889 align:middle line:84%
in small part, because
Boasberg didn't enter

00:47:06.889 --> 00:47:08.680 align:middle line:84%
a temporary restraining
order against them,

00:47:08.680 --> 00:47:09.930 align:middle line:90%
which he should have.

00:47:09.930 --> 00:47:11.760 align:middle line:84%
And so there's been
a lot of cheering

00:47:11.760 --> 00:47:13.140 align:middle line:84%
going on now that
he has declared

00:47:13.140 --> 00:47:15.030 align:middle line:90%
that that was unlawful.

00:47:15.030 --> 00:47:16.620 align:middle line:84%
But the problem
is that because he

00:47:16.620 --> 00:47:20.104 align:middle line:84%
had allowed it to
go to completion,

00:47:20.104 --> 00:47:22.020 align:middle line:84%
the issue that we really
have to deal with now

00:47:22.020 --> 00:47:25.140 align:middle line:84%
is that he has said that
there were three major areas

00:47:25.140 --> 00:47:28.890 align:middle line:84%
that the US Army Corps of
Engineers and the Environmental

00:47:28.890 --> 00:47:33.262 align:middle line:84%
Protection Agency of the Trump
administration did not consider

00:47:33.262 --> 00:47:35.220 align:middle line:90%
and they have to consider those.

00:47:35.220 --> 00:47:38.490 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that Judge
Boasberg, in the same opinion,

00:47:38.490 --> 00:47:43.230 align:middle line:84%
has stated that, even if now
in retrospect the Environmental

00:47:43.230 --> 00:47:46.200 align:middle line:84%
Protection Agency and the
US Army Corps of Engineers

00:47:46.200 --> 00:47:48.780 align:middle line:84%
do go back and look
at those issues

00:47:48.780 --> 00:47:50.950 align:middle line:84%
and whatever they say--
oh, we've looked at them

00:47:50.950 --> 00:47:53.700 align:middle line:84%
and we still determine
that even if we had given

00:47:53.700 --> 00:47:55.200 align:middle line:84%
full consideration
of this, we still

00:47:55.200 --> 00:47:56.950 align:middle line:84%
should have gotten the
easement, we should

00:47:56.950 --> 00:47:58.080 align:middle line:90%
have granted the easement.

00:47:58.080 --> 00:47:59.460 align:middle line:84%
And they say, so
therefore, we're

00:47:59.460 --> 00:48:02.327 align:middle line:84%
going to remedy those things,
we've considered them,

00:48:02.327 --> 00:48:04.410 align:middle line:84%
and we don't think they're
adequately serious that

00:48:04.410 --> 00:48:06.010 align:middle line:90%
should stop the pipeline.

00:48:06.010 --> 00:48:09.400 align:middle line:84%
And so it's not going to
get you anywhere after that.

00:48:09.400 --> 00:48:13.800 align:middle line:84%
And he has said that the court
has very limited authority

00:48:13.800 --> 00:48:17.280 align:middle line:84%
to gainsay the kind
of subjective decision

00:48:17.280 --> 00:48:19.620 align:middle line:84%
that the agency is going
to make about that.

00:48:19.620 --> 00:48:21.715 align:middle line:84%
And he has said that
elections have consequences--

00:48:21.715 --> 00:48:23.490 align:middle line:84%
he actually said
it in his opinion--

00:48:23.490 --> 00:48:24.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:48:24.290 --> 00:48:24.930 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:48:24.930 --> 00:48:26.370 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And that
therefore if they

00:48:26.370 --> 00:48:28.500 align:middle line:84%
have a judgment that even
after they've considered

00:48:28.500 --> 00:48:31.930 align:middle line:84%
those things, they still should
have granted the easement,

00:48:31.930 --> 00:48:33.850 align:middle line:84%
then the easement
will still be valid.

00:48:33.850 --> 00:48:38.580 align:middle line:84%
So the question that will be
in front of him on June 21,

00:48:38.580 --> 00:48:43.830 align:middle line:84%
is whether or not he should stop
the flow of oil in the pipeline

00:48:43.830 --> 00:48:47.550 align:middle line:84%
while those considerations
are being evaluated.

00:48:47.550 --> 00:48:50.640 align:middle line:84%
And I personally don't
believe he's going to do that.

00:48:50.640 --> 00:48:52.140 align:middle line:84%
Because the fact
is it isn't going

00:48:52.140 --> 00:48:55.590 align:middle line:84%
to take the Trump administration
EPA and the US Army

00:48:55.590 --> 00:48:58.620 align:middle line:84%
Corps of Engineers very long to
turn and look at those things

00:48:58.620 --> 00:49:00.510 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, we've
given those a good look,

00:49:00.510 --> 00:49:02.430 align:middle line:84%
we don't think those
are troublesome at all.

00:49:02.430 --> 00:49:05.760 align:middle line:84%
And so now we have checked
those little boxes,

00:49:05.760 --> 00:49:08.460 align:middle line:84%
we've crossed the t and
dotted the i on those things

00:49:08.460 --> 00:49:10.305 align:middle line:84%
that we might have
slipped up on before.

00:49:10.305 --> 00:49:11.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the
oil keeps flowing.

00:49:11.110 --> 00:49:13.146 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And then
the oil keeps flowing.

00:49:13.146 --> 00:49:14.520 align:middle line:84%
And so that what
we're faced with

00:49:14.520 --> 00:49:17.310 align:middle line:84%
is a series of
some 800 people who

00:49:17.310 --> 00:49:20.640 align:middle line:84%
have been arrested and
charged with crimes

00:49:20.640 --> 00:49:22.840 align:middle line:90%
by the state of North Dakota.

00:49:22.840 --> 00:49:27.180 align:middle line:84%
And some 150 of them,
180 of them now,

00:49:27.180 --> 00:49:30.150 align:middle line:84%
have been dismissed
by the judges

00:49:30.150 --> 00:49:32.220 align:middle line:84%
of them having absolutely
no evidence whatsoever

00:49:32.220 --> 00:49:33.720 align:middle line:90%
against those people.

00:49:33.720 --> 00:49:37.350 align:middle line:84%
But there's still a
remaining 600 people or so.

00:49:37.350 --> 00:49:39.300 align:middle line:84%
There's about 50 of them
who have been charged

00:49:39.300 --> 00:49:40.785 align:middle line:90%
with serious felony crimes.

00:49:40.785 --> 00:49:42.660 align:middle line:84%
But there's only
one person who's

00:49:42.660 --> 00:49:45.780 align:middle line:84%
been charged with
inciting the riot,

00:49:45.780 --> 00:49:48.690 align:middle line:84%
instigating the insurrection
against the state of North

00:49:48.690 --> 00:49:51.590 align:middle line:84%
Dakota as it were,
and that's Chase Iron

00:49:51.590 --> 00:49:54.710 align:middle line:84%
Eyes, the Democratic
Party nominee.

00:49:54.710 --> 00:49:56.550 align:middle line:84%
The National Democratic
Party nominee

00:49:56.550 --> 00:50:00.660 align:middle line:84%
for the 2016 congressional
race for the one single seat

00:50:00.660 --> 00:50:02.880 align:middle line:84%
in Congress, in the
House of Representatives

00:50:02.880 --> 00:50:04.320 align:middle line:90%
that the state has.

00:50:04.320 --> 00:50:06.330 align:middle line:84%
He has been charged
with instigating

00:50:06.330 --> 00:50:09.690 align:middle line:84%
the entire insurrection
against the state.

00:50:09.690 --> 00:50:12.210 align:middle line:90%
And I'm representing him.

00:50:12.210 --> 00:50:15.450 align:middle line:84%
And I'll be representing a
couple of the other people that

00:50:15.450 --> 00:50:19.950 align:middle line:84%
have been charged with
participating in the riot.

00:50:19.950 --> 00:50:22.980 align:middle line:84%
And he's also been charged
with trespassing, interestingly

00:50:22.980 --> 00:50:25.140 align:middle line:84%
enough, on land
where his people have

00:50:25.140 --> 00:50:27.960 align:middle line:84%
been for hundreds
and hundreds of years

00:50:27.960 --> 00:50:30.510 align:middle line:84%
prior to the US government
insisting they have

00:50:30.510 --> 00:50:32.680 align:middle line:90%
taken control of that land.

00:50:32.680 --> 00:50:34.800 align:middle line:84%
So there are a number
of major issues

00:50:34.800 --> 00:50:36.830 align:middle line:90%
that are still at stake here.

00:50:36.830 --> 00:50:38.430 align:middle line:84%
There are other
people to be tried.

00:50:38.430 --> 00:50:40.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm just representing
a small handful

00:50:40.980 --> 00:50:42.847 align:middle line:84%
of the people that
have key charges that

00:50:42.847 --> 00:50:45.180 align:middle line:84%
have been made against them
that give us the opportunity

00:50:45.180 --> 00:50:48.569 align:middle line:84%
to raise these
fundamental challenges.

00:50:48.569 --> 00:50:50.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh my gosh, of
course, we've run out of time.

00:50:50.860 --> 00:50:53.370 align:middle line:84%
I want to just tease--
just a little tease--

00:50:53.370 --> 00:50:55.590 align:middle line:84%
the Monterey Community
Energy Company and what's

00:50:55.590 --> 00:50:57.090 align:middle line:84%
happening down
there, because you've

00:50:57.090 --> 00:51:01.211 align:middle line:84%
managed to take back control
over your own power company.

00:51:01.211 --> 00:51:02.210 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:51:02.210 --> 00:51:04.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk about that
for two minutes, because we're

00:51:04.380 --> 00:51:04.670 align:middle line:90%
over.

00:51:04.670 --> 00:51:06.253 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: In the
state of California,

00:51:06.253 --> 00:51:09.080 align:middle line:84%
under the leadership of
Governor Jerry Brown,

00:51:09.080 --> 00:51:12.000 align:middle line:84%
we have passed legislation
that authorizes each county

00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:16.290 align:middle line:84%
in the state of California
to set up its own independent

00:51:16.290 --> 00:51:18.990 align:middle line:84%
community choice
energy company--

00:51:18.990 --> 00:51:21.015 align:middle line:84%
publicly owned, not by
private stockholders

00:51:21.015 --> 00:51:23.020 align:middle line:84%
and not-for-profit--
and that they

00:51:23.020 --> 00:51:25.870 align:middle line:84%
can purchase completely
clean energy from wind

00:51:25.870 --> 00:51:28.180 align:middle line:90%
and solar and tidal power.

00:51:28.180 --> 00:51:30.790 align:middle line:84%
And what we've done now is
we've established the largest

00:51:30.790 --> 00:51:34.420 align:middle line:84%
community choice energy company
in the country-- in the world

00:51:34.420 --> 00:51:36.400 align:middle line:84%
actually-- for the
entire three counties

00:51:36.400 --> 00:51:40.180 align:middle line:84%
around Monterey, and Santa
Cruz, and San Benito.

00:51:40.180 --> 00:51:41.770 align:middle line:84%
We're now going
to be expanding it

00:51:41.770 --> 00:51:45.590 align:middle line:84%
down south into San
Luis Obispo and Ventura

00:51:45.590 --> 00:51:47.170 align:middle line:90%
and down in San Diego.

00:51:47.170 --> 00:51:49.070 align:middle line:84%
And it's been moving
up north-- it's

00:51:49.070 --> 00:51:50.687 align:middle line:90%
now up in northern California.

00:51:50.687 --> 00:51:52.270 align:middle line:84%
We're going to move
up the coast line.

00:51:52.270 --> 00:51:54.478 align:middle line:84%
We're going to get the state
of Oregon and Washington

00:51:54.478 --> 00:51:56.020 align:middle line:90%
to pass these statutes.

00:51:56.020 --> 00:51:58.850 align:middle line:84%
And what we're doing is we're
replacing the Pacific Gas

00:51:58.850 --> 00:52:03.280 align:middle line:84%
and Electric Company
that is still using coal

00:52:03.280 --> 00:52:05.371 align:middle line:90%
and petroleum and natural gas--

00:52:05.371 --> 00:52:07.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and
the rates they charge.

00:52:07.120 --> 00:52:08.578 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And in
fact, we're going

00:52:08.578 --> 00:52:11.830 align:middle line:84%
to be selling the
electricity for only 3/4

00:52:11.830 --> 00:52:13.950 align:middle line:84%
of what it costs
for the dirty fuel.

00:52:13.950 --> 00:52:16.900 align:middle line:84%
And also, we've gotten the
churches and synagogues

00:52:16.900 --> 00:52:18.700 align:middle line:84%
of all the denominations
that are now

00:52:18.700 --> 00:52:22.480 align:middle line:84%
starting to agree to put solar
panels on all of their churches

00:52:22.480 --> 00:52:24.405 align:middle line:90%
and houses of worship.

00:52:24.405 --> 00:52:25.780 align:middle line:84%
I keep trying to
get them to call

00:52:25.780 --> 00:52:28.150 align:middle line:90%
it the divine light and power.

00:52:28.150 --> 00:52:29.080 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:29.080 --> 00:52:30.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:52:30.010 --> 00:52:32.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: But the bottom line
is that we have now 48 churches

00:52:32.890 --> 00:52:34.180 align:middle line:90%
that are--

00:52:34.180 --> 00:52:37.840 align:middle line:84%
the Catholic churches have
led the way on this, because

00:52:37.840 --> 00:52:40.960 align:middle line:84%
of Pope Francis' global
encyclical on global climate

00:52:40.960 --> 00:52:42.010 align:middle line:90%
change.

00:52:42.010 --> 00:52:45.190 align:middle line:84%
So they've agreed to give--
the diocese in Monterey agreed

00:52:45.190 --> 00:52:47.290 align:middle line:84%
to give loans to
all the churches

00:52:47.290 --> 00:52:50.699 align:middle line:84%
to pay for putting
these on their roofs.

00:52:50.699 --> 00:52:52.990 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to be
generating more power than they

00:52:52.990 --> 00:52:55.650 align:middle line:84%
really need to pay
for years and then

00:52:55.650 --> 00:52:59.450 align:middle line:84%
selling it for one third of its
price to the energy company.

00:52:59.450 --> 00:53:01.299 align:middle line:84%
And then they can
sell it for only 3/4

00:53:01.299 --> 00:53:02.590 align:middle line:90%
of what they would have to pay.

00:53:02.590 --> 00:53:04.540 align:middle line:84%
So everybody is
saving money on this.

00:53:04.540 --> 00:53:08.710 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to reduce by
90% the global greenhouse gas

00:53:08.710 --> 00:53:10.840 align:middle line:84%
emissions within 10
years in California.

00:53:10.840 --> 00:53:11.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Love it.

00:53:11.710 --> 00:53:12.510 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:53:12.510 --> 00:53:13.990 align:middle line:84%
We had to get that in
before the end of the show.

00:53:13.990 --> 00:53:16.573 align:middle line:84%
Because we were going to spend
a lot of time talking about it,

00:53:16.573 --> 00:53:17.422 align:middle line:90%
but there you go.

00:53:17.422 --> 00:53:19.880 align:middle line:84%
The other thing I would like
to talk to you down the road--

00:53:19.880 --> 00:53:22.300 align:middle line:84%
